{
  "stem": "27509.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he used to come every Saturday to visit his mother, Saturday afternoon, which was a set piece of-- of family interaction.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we as children looked forward to it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And even if the discussion usually turned down always on the same subject.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and they women were about talking about their-- their domestics and all those things, as it is normal, the things that are on people's minds.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My grandfather, on the-- that's my mother's father-- was-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] he was-- he had cataracts on both his eyes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was a scholar.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And on-- although he could hardly read, he had to put his-- his hand over his eyes to shade it to be able to-- to fetch anything or catch anything in small print.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He used to give a daily schul, a daily a lesson in Talmud by heart to go on up-- to his grown up congregation without fail.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when I was at the age of 11, 12, the summer months when all the boys were running around with their-- what sort of games they could find in the street, my father insisted that on the Sunday mornings I had to go every day to my grandfather's home.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he used to sit with me in the-- in the attic and teaching-- giving me a lesson in Talmud, day in and day out, for a couple of hours every day.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Never looking into-- into the volume.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Never looking into the book, and so on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But otherwise, he was in retirement, living with his son's family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my father--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Judel, or Yehudal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] As I've indicated a minute ago, he was an orphan.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he grew up with his older brother.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
